Returns true of the digits reprented by input sequence 1 are less than the digits represented by input sequence 2.

Parameters:
b1 an iterator to the beginning of input sequence 1(inclusive)
e1 an iterator to the end of input sequence 1(exclusive)
b2 an iterator to the beginning of input sequence 2(inclusive)
e2 an iterator to the end of input sequence 2(exclusive)
Returns:
True iff the s1's digits are less than s2's digits.
Note:
Assumes the iterators are iterating such that bX points at the LEAST significant digit, and eX points just past the MOST significant byte.
